**65. Explain HTTP status codes.** 
HTTP status codes are three-digit numbers sent by web servers to browsers. They tell the 
browser whether an internet request was successful or failed completely. For example, a 200 OK 
code means the request worked perfectly as expected. A 404 Not Found code means the 
requested webpage does not exist anywhere. Codes star ng with 5 mean there is a serious 
error on the server side. They help developers debug network connec on problems during 
applica on development cycles. 
