**68. What are the main advantages of modular JavaScript?** 
Modular JavaScript allows developers to break giant code files into separate smaller modules. 
Each module has a specific small job and operates independently from others. You can export 
code from one module and import it into another file. The main advantage is that it makes code 
much easier to organize over me. It prevents variable name conflicts because each module has 
its own local scope. It also allows large development teams to work on separate features 
simultaneously. 
